ing a Basic Lashing on yourself with your Gravitation surge, spend 1 focus to gain , which can be used only for Division or one of its talents.','Free Action',0,1,0,'You excel at using Division while sweeping through the air with Gravitation.',23),(296,'Invested(Skybreaker)','When you acquire this talent, your maximum Investiture increases by a number equal to your tier. When your tier increases by 1, your maximum Investiture does as well.','Passive',0,0,0,'You learn to hold and wield greater quantities of Stormlight within yourself.',23),(297,'Wound Regeneration(Skybreaker)','When you use the Regenerate free action, you can spend Investiture to instantly recover from an injury of your choice (either instead of or in addition to healing yourself). Spend 2 Investiture to recover from a temporary injury, or spend 3 Investiture to recover from a permanent one.','Special',0,0,2,'You can use Stormlight to rapidly recover from injuries.',23),(298,'Deepened Bond(Skybreaker)','Your spren bond range increases from 30 feet to 100 feet. Additionally, when you spend focus to give your spren a task, it costs you 1 fewer focus (to a minimum cost of 1).','Passive',0,0,0,'The strength of your Nahel bond now allows your spren to manifest more fully in the Physical Realm.',23),(299,'Take Squire(Skybreaker)','After a long rest, choose a companion or player character you can influence to take as your squire. To choose them, they must be willing and sapient, you must have known them for at least 1 game session, and they must not have bonded a Radiant spren. When you choose a squire, decide whether you want to grant them both of your surges, one of them, or none. That character becomes your squire, gaining the surges you chose plus the other benefits in the “Squires” section earlier in this chapter. You can have a maximum number of squires up to your current Ideal (such as three for the Third Ideal). If you already have the maximum number of squires, you must choose one to dismiss as your squire before choosing a new one.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin taking other people under your wing, allowing them to breathe Stormlight and use surges before they’ve established their own Nahel bond.',23),(300,'First Ideal (Stoneward Key)','When you acquire this talent, you gain access to Investiture, beginning with a maximum Investiture of 2 + your Awareness or Presence (whichever is higher). You can now use the Breathe Stormlight, Enhance, and Regenerate actions. Additionally, you gain the goal “Speak the First Ideal.” After you  complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You gain the   Cohesion and Tension surges. ◆ You gain an additional skill on your character sheet for the above surges, starting with 1 rank in each.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin bonding an peakspren, allowing you to breathe in and use Stormlight. You might be aware of this nascent bond, or you might use the powers subconsciously until you get closer to speaking the First Ideal.',24),(301,'Second Ideal (Stoneward)','You gain the goal “Speak the Second Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ Your Enhance action becomes more powerful. While you have 1 Investiture or more, you can use Enhance as (free action), and you don’t need to spend Investiture to use this action or maintain its effect.','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to deepen your Nahel bond with your peakspren by speaking the Second Ideal.',24),(302,'Third Ideal (Stoneward)','You gain the goal “Speak the Third Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can summon your spren as a Radiant Shardblade (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to advance your Nahel bond even further by speaking the Third Ideal.',24),(303,'Fourth Ideal (Stoneward)','You gain the goal “Speak the Fourth Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can call a swarm of bindspren as Radiant Shardplate (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to become a full Knight Radiant by speaking the Fourth Ideal.',24),(304,'Cohesive Teamwork','After you use the Gain Advantage action while having 1 Investiture or more, whether you succeed or fail, the next test an ally makes against that target gains an advantage. Until the end of your next turn, while standing on stone, you can’t be moved against your will or knocked Prone.','Passive',0,1,0,'Stonewards strive to exemplify determination and teamwork. Their resolve shows allies where to intuitively hold the line.',24),(305,'Invested(Stoneward)','When you acquire this talent, your maximum Investiture increases by a number equal to your tier. When your tier increases by 1, your maximum Investiture does as well.','Passive',0,0,0,'You learn to hold and wield greater quantities of Stormlight within yourself.',24),(306,'Wound Regeneration(Stoneward)','When you use the Regenerate free action, you can spend Investiture to instantly recover from an injury of your choice (either instead of or in addition to healing yourself). Spend 2 Investiture to recover from a temporary injury, or spend 3 Investiture to recover from a permanent one.','Special',0,0,2,'You can use Stormlight to rapidly recover from injuries.',24),(307,'Deepened Bond(Stoneward)','Your spren bond range increases from 30 feet to 100 feet. Additionally, when you spend focus to give your spren a task, it costs you 1 fewer focus (to a minimum cost of 1).','Passive',0,0,0,'The strength of your Nahel bond now allows your spren to manifest more fully in the Physical Realm.',24),(308,'Take Squire(Stoneward)','After a long rest, choose a companion or player character you can influence to take as your squire. To choose them, they must be willing and sapient, you must have known them for at least 1 game session, and they must not have bonded a Radiant spren. When you choose a squire, decide whether you want to grant them both of your surges, one of them, or none. That character becomes your squire, gaining the surges you chose plus the other benefits in the “Squires” section earlier in this chapter. As a Stoneward, you can have a maximum number of squires up to your current level. If you already have the maximum number of squires, you must choose one to dismiss as your squire before choosing a new one.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin taking other people under your wing, allowing them to breathe Stormlight and use surges before they’ve established their own Nahel bond.',24),(309,'First Ideal (Truthwatcher Key)','When you acquire this talent, you gain access to Investiture, beginning with a maximum Investiture of 2 + your Awareness or Presence (whichever is higher). You can now use the Breathe Stormlight, Enhance, and Regenerate actions. Additionally, you gain the goal “Speak the First Ideal.” After you  complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You gain the Illumination and Progression surges. ◆ You gain an additional skill on your character sheet for the above surges, starting with 1 rank in each.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin bonding an mistspren, allowing you to breathe in and use Stormlight. You might be aware of this nascent bond, or you might use the powers subconsciously until you get closer to speaking the First Ideal.',25),(310,'Second Ideal (Truthwatcher)','You gain the goal “Speak the Second Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ Your Enhance action becomes more powerful. While you have 1 Investiture or more, you can use Enhance as (free action), and you don’t need to spend Investiture to use this action or maintain its effect.','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to deepen your Nahel bond with your mistspren by speaking the Second Ideal.',25),(311,'Third Ideal (Truthwatcher)','You gain the goal “Speak the Third Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can summon your spren as a Radiant Shardblade (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to advance your Nahel bond even further by speaking the Third Ideal.',25),(312,'Fourth Ideal (Truthwatcher)','You gain the goal “Speak the Fourth Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can call a swarm of concentrationspren as Radiant Shardplate (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to become a full Knight Radiant by speaking the Fourth Ideal.',25),(313,'Spiritual Healing','Before you restore health to yourself or a willing ally, you can spend 2 Investiture to instead cause the target to recover half as much focus (rounded up) as they would have recovered health.','Special',0,1,0,'You mix Illumination and Regrowth to skillfully repair the mind and soul.',25),(314,'Invested(Truthwatcher)','When you acquire this talent, your maximum Investiture increases by a number equal to your tier. When your tier increases by 1, your maximum Investiture does as well.','Passive',0,0,0,'You learn to hold and wield greater quantities of Stormlight within yourself.',25),(315,'Wound Regeneration(Truthwatcher)','When you use the Regenerate free action, you can spend Investiture to instantly recover from an injury of your choice (either instead of or in addition to healing yourself). Spend 2 Investiture to recover from a temporary injury, or spend 3 Investiture to recover from a permanent one.','Special',0,0,2,'You can use Stormlight to rapidly recover from injuries.',25),(316,'Deepened Bond(Truthwatcher)','Your spren bond range increases from 30 feet to 100 feet. Additionally, when you spend focus to give your spren a task, it costs you 1 fewer focus (to a minimum cost of 1).','Passive',0,0,0,'The strength of your Nahel bond now allows your spren to manifest more fully in the Physical Realm.',25),(317,'Take Squire(Truthwatcher)','After a long rest, choose a companion or player character you can influence to take as your squire. To choose them, they must be willing and sapient, you must have known them for at least 1 game session, and they must not have bonded a Radiant spren. When you choose a squire, decide whether you want to grant them both of your surges, one of them, or none. That character becomes your squire, gaining the surges you chose plus the other benefits in the “Squires” section earlier in this chapter. You can have a maximum number of squires up to your current Ideal (such as three for the Third Ideal). If you already have the maximum number of squires, you must choose one to dismiss as your squire before choosing a new one.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin taking other people under your wing, allowing them to breathe Stormlight and use surges before they’ve established their own Nahel bond.',25),(318,'First Ideal (Willshaper Key)','When you acquire this talent, you gain access to Investiture, beginning with a maximum Investiture of 2 + your Awareness or Presence (whichever is higher). You can now use the Breathe Stormlight, Enhance, and Regenerate actions. Additionally, you gain the goal “Speak the First Ideal.” After you  complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You gain the Cohesion and Transportation surges. ◆ You gain an additional skill on your character sheet for the above surges, starting with 1 rank in each.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin bonding an lightspren, allowing you to breathe in and use Stormlight. You might be aware of this nascent bond, or you might use the powers subconsciously until you get closer to speaking the First Ideal.',26),(319,'Second Ideal (Willshaper)','You gain the goal “Speak the Second Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ Your Enhance action becomes more powerful. While you have 1 Investiture or more, you can use Enhance as (free action), and you don’t need to spend Investiture to use this action or maintain its effect.','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to deepen your Nahel bond with your lightspren by speaking the Second Ideal.',26),(320,'Third Ideal (Willshaper)','You gain the goal “Speak the Third Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can summon your spren as a Radiant Shardblade (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to advance your Nahel bond even further by speaking the Third Ideal.',26),(321,'Fourth Ideal (Willshaper)','You gain the goal “Speak the Fourth Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can call a swarm of joyspren as Radiant Shardplate (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to become a full Knight Radiant by speaking the Fourth Ideal.',26),(322,'Spiritual Cohesion','Once per scene, choose one or more allies you can influence, up to a number equaling your current Ideal (such as two allies for the Second Ideal). Each target becomes Determined until the end of the scene. If a target uses that condition to add an Opportunity to a test, increase their Cognitive defense and Spiritual defense by 2 until the end of the scene.','Action',2,0,0,'Willshapers lead by example, raising the spirits of those around them through radical acts of self-expression.',26),(323,'Invested(Willshaper)','When you acquire this talent, your maximum Investiture increases by a number equal to your tier. When your tier increases by 1, your maximum Investiture does as well.','Passive',0,0,0,'You learn to hold and wield greater quantities of Stormlight within yourself.',26),(324,'Wound Regeneration(Willshaper)','When you use the Regenerate free action, you can spend Investiture to instantly recover from an injury of your choice (either instead of or in addition to healing yourself). Spend 2 Investiture to recover from a temporary injury, or spend 3 Investiture to recover from a permanent one.','Special',0,0,2,'You can use Stormlight to rapidly recover from injuries.',26),(325,'Deepened Bond(Willshaper)','Your spren bond range increases from 30 feet to 100 feet. Additionally, when you spend focus to give your spren a task, it costs you 1 fewer focus (to a minimum cost of 1).','Passive',0,0,0,'The strength of your Nahel bond now allows your spren to manifest more fully in the Physical Realm.',26),(326,'Take Squire(Willshaper)','After a long rest, choose a companion or player character you can influence to take as your squire. To choose them, they must be willing and sapient, you must have known them for at least 1 game session, and they must not have bonded a Radiant spren. When you choose a squire, decide whether you want to grant them both of your surges, one of them, or none. That character becomes your squire, gaining the surges you chose plus the other benefits in the “Squires” section earlier in this chapter. You can have a maximum number of squires up to your current Ideal (such as three for the Third Ideal). If you already have the maximum number of squires, you must choose one to dismiss as your squire before choosing a new one.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin taking other people under your wing, allowing them to breathe Stormlight and use surges before they’ve established their own Nahel bond.',26),(327,'First Ideal (Windrunner Key)','When you acquire this talent, you gain access to Investiture, beginning with a maximum Investiture of 2 + your Awareness or Presence (whichever is higher). You can now use the Breathe Stormlight, Enhance, and Regenerate actions. Additionally, you gain the goal “Speak the First Ideal.” After you  complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You gain the Adhesion and Gravitation surges. ◆ You gain an additional skill on your character sheet for the above surges, starting with 1 rank in each.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin bonding an honorspren, allowing you to breathe in and use Stormlight. You might be aware of this nascent bond, or you might use the powers subconsciously until you get closer to speaking the First Ideal.',27),(328,'Second Ideal (Windrunner)','You gain the goal “Speak the Second Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ Your Enhance action becomes more powerful. While you have 1 Investiture or more, you can use Enhance as (free action), and you don’t need to spend Investiture to use this action or maintain its effect.','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to deepen your Nahel bond with your honorspren by speaking the Second Ideal.',27),(329,'Third Ideal (Windrunner)','You gain the goal “Speak the Third Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can summon your spren as a Radiant Shardblade (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to advance your Nahel bond even further by speaking the Third Ideal.',27),(330,'Fourth Ideal (Windrunner)','You gain the goal “Speak the Fourth Ideal.” After you complete this goal, you gain the following reward: ◆ You become Empowered until the end of that scene. ◆ You can call a swarm of windspren as Radiant Shardplate (see chapter 7).','Special',0,0,0,'You seek to become a full Knight Radiant by speaking the Fourth Ideal.',27),(331,'Reverse Lashing','Before you infuse yourself or an object with a Basic Lashing using your Gravitation surge, you can instead infuse the target with a Reverse Lashing using Adhesion. When you do, declare a type of object (such as “projectiles,” “gems,” or “keys”) for the infused target to attract. Only unattended, unsecuredobjects can be attracted, and each must be of a size you can affect with your ranks in Adhesion (see the Surge Scaling table in chapter 6). When those objects come within a number of feet equal to your gravitation rate, they fly straight toward and stick to the infused target; this can divert ranged attacks from their intended targets. An attracted objectremains on the infused target until the infusion ends or until the object is removed.','Special',1,0,1,'You can infuse things with a mix of Adhesion and Gravitation, giving them a weak gravitational pull on specific objects.',27),(332,'Invested(Windrunner)','When you acquire this talent, your maximum Investiture increases by a number equal to your tier. When your tier increases by 1, your maximum Investiture does as well.','Passive',0,0,0,'You learn to hold and wield greater quantities of Stormlight within yourself.',27),(333,'Wound Regeneration(Windrunner)','When you use the Regenerate free action, you can spend Investiture to instantly recover from an injury of your choice (either instead of or in addition to healing yourself). Spend 2 Investiture to recover from a temporary injury, or spend 3 Investiture to recover from a permanent one.','Special',0,0,2,'You can use Stormlight to rapidly recover from injuries.',27),(334,'Deepened Bond(Windrunner)','Your spren bond range increases from 30 feet to 100 feet. Additionally, when you spend focus to give your spren a task, it costs you 1 fewer focus (to a minimum cost of 1).','Passive',0,0,0,'The strength of your Nahel bond now allows your spren to manifest more fully in the Physical Realm.',27),(335,'Take Squire(Windrunner)','After a long rest, choose a companion or player character you can influence to take as your squire. To choose them, they must be willing and sapient, you must have known them for at least 1 game session, and they must not have bonded a Radiant spren. When you choose a squire, decide whether you want to grant them both of your surges, one of them, or none. That character becomes your squire, gaining the surges you chose plus the other benefits in the “Squires” section earlier in this chapter. As a Windrunner, you can have a maximum number of squires up to twice your level. If you already have the maximum number of squires, you must choose one to dismiss as your squire before choosing a new one.','Special',0,0,0,'You begin taking other people under your wing, allowing them to breathe Stormlight and use surges before they’ve established their own Nahel bond.',27);
